news.title: Improved Measurements Might Unveil Unknown 95 Percent Of Universe’s Building Blocks
news.synopsis: Only five percent of the substances that make up our visible universe and everything around us are provisionally understood and described by science. CERN is the world’s largest particle physics test facility. Here, on the outskirts of Geneva, researches look for the remaining 95 percent of the universe’s substances by beaming particles against one other in collisions that create a type of ‘mini-Big Bang ‘.

news.title: Leighton Vander Esch named NFC Defensive Player of the Week
news.synopsis: Those who didn't know how impactful the rookie linebacker had been for the Dallas Cowboys this season got an eye-full when the bright lights of Sunday Night Football came on, facing the Philadelphia Eagles in a must-win scenario without All-Pro linebacker Sean Lee in tow. It's the fourth game Lee has missed this season with nagging hamstring injuries, and it won't be his last, his absence predicted to stretch upwards of six weeks. If that holds firm, he'll end up having been sidelined nine of 16 regular season games, a keen reminder of why the Cowboys selected Vander Esch with the 19th-overall pick in the first place.

news.title: Amazon’s $150,000 Jobs Herald New Era Tripling Nashville Incomes
news.synopsis: Music City is set to continue its multiyear boom after landing a 5,000-person operations center from Amazon.com Inc.  The Internet giant will become one of Nashville, Tennessee’s biggest employers with news Tuesday that Amazon will open a $230 million facility in downtown, with average wages more than $150,000 -- or triple the city’s median household income. While its Amazon haul pales in comparison to the 25,000 jobs bound for each of New York and Arlington, Virginia, its presence could affect life in Nashville almost as much on a relative basis.
